        <h2>Yugm's all time favourite destination_</h2>
        <h5>Nanda Devi, one of the most iconic mountains in Uttarakhand_ _</h5>
        <p>


            Nanda Devi, located in the Garhwal Himalayas, is the 23rd highest mountain in the world and the highest peak in Uttarakhand. 
            Standing tall at 7,816 meters above sea level, this mountain is a trekkers' paradise and a sacred pilgrimage site for Hindus.
             The Nanda Devi National Park, 
            surrounding the peak, is home to a variety of flora and fauna, including rare species like the Himalayan brown bear and the snow leopard. 
            The trek to the base camp of Nanda Devi is a challenging but breathtaking journey,
             offering stunning views of the surrounding peaks and glaciers.</p>
